text.tspan: Assembly Manual TurboLEDz 88s
Thank you for supporting TurboLEDz. Before you start assembly, please note
that components will be soldered on both sides of the PCB. The LED bars will
be mounted on the front (where the TurboLEDz logo is.) All the other com-
ponents will be mounted on the back (where there are pre-mounted SMD ICs.)
Solder the IC at U2, making sure to observe the
orientation. The notch points down to the bottom
edge of the board.
Note: you have to bend the IC pins inwards a little
to insert them into the PCB.
Bend the resistor legs and solder at R1. Solder the
capacitor at EC1. Neither part has polarity, so
orientation does not matter.
Flip the board and mount all the LED bars (on the
PCB-side with the TurboLEDz logo, and diode
symbols.) CHECK FOR BENT PINS before inserting.
WARNING! Observe orientation. The printed side of
the bars with model nr, go to the left. Pin 1 is at the
printed side. The LED bar also has 1 very slight
bevelled edge which denotes pin1, and corresponds
to the square solder-pad on the PCB.
Do not mount these in the wrong orientation: it will
result in unsalvagable e-waste if you do.
Flip the board again, and clip all excess lengths of
the LED bar leads (after soldering.)
Then, solder the 12-pin header to the back of the
board (With the Vcc ACL LAT CLK SIN annotations.)
Solder only 1 side of the micro-controller to the
header (pads RAW,GND,RST,VCC...10) at the top-
end of the header pins.
Use a temporary spacer to mount the controller
up high. (e.g. creditcards or cardboard to space.)
CHECK: Printed side faces AWAY from the logo.
